{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "The era\u2019s zero tolerance of drug users helped lead to a life term for Lenny Singleton, one of tens of thousands of such inmates across the country....", "abstract": "Nearly 160,000 prisoners in United States are serving life sentences, number that has quadrupled since 1984, leading to calls for release of inmates who committed crimes in which no one was hurt; drug addict Lenny Singleton was sentenced to two life sentences, plus 100 additional years, with no possibility for parole when he robbed 13 stores over eight days in 1995, crime spree in which no one was hurt.", "section_name": "U.S.", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Timothy", "role": "reported", "lastname": "WILLIAMS", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By TIMOTHY WILLIAMS"}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/07/05/us/mass-incarceration-drug-offenses-zero-tolerance-prisons.html", "lead_paragraph": "The era\u2019s zero tolerance of drug users helped lead to a life term for Lenny Singleton, one of tens of thousands of such inmates across the country.", "headline": {"main": "One Robber\u2019s 3 Life Sentences: \u201990s Legacy Fills Prisons Today", "print_headline": "A \u201990s Legacy That Is Filling  Prisons Today"}, "_id": "577ade2f38f0d83e1f65d6f2", "word_count": "1249", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/05/29/us/30massincarceration-web1/30massincarceration-web1-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/05/29/us/30massincarceration-web1/30massincarceration-web1-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 400, "url": "images/2016/05/29/us/30massincarceration-web1/30massincarceration-web1-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/05/29/us/30massincarceration-web1/30massincarceration-web1-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "400"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "typ